						<summary>

						<p>Slab fixed in the ceiling of the temple of Chennakēśavasvāmi.</p>						

						<p>1727 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Śaka 1650, Plāvaṅga, Chaitra śu. 10, March 10, 1727 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records the offerings of ten thousand <hi rend="italic">namaskārams</hi> daily to the God Cheṁnna Kēśavarasvāmi at Dāmgaṭla by certain Śarabhanna, the stone cutter (Kāśutal) of Yallāla.</p>						

